questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Given below are four jumbled parts of a sentence. Select the option that gives their correct order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A) by the elaborate design of&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B) the scientist was intrigued&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C) that shape universal laws&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D) cosmic phenomena&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option (3)&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;strong&gt;BADC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence begins with the primary subject and verb &amp;quot;The scientist was intrigued,&amp;quot; which is &lt;strong&gt;part (B).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Following the verb, the prepositional phrase &amp;quot;by the elaborate design of&amp;quot; &lt;strong&gt;(BA)&lt;/strong&gt; explains what caused the scientist&amp;#39;s intrigue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The next part,&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;cosmic phenomena,&amp;quot; &lt;strong&gt;(D)&lt;/strong&gt; acts as the object of the preposition &amp;quot;of,&amp;quot; identifying what was elaborately designed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ending with &lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;that shape universal laws&amp;quot; &lt;strong&gt;(C)&lt;/strong&gt; provides a relative clause that describes the significance of the cosmic phenomena.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the logical and grammatical sequence is: &lt;strong&gt;BADC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 (ABCD):&lt;/strong&gt; This starts with &amp;quot;by the elaborate design of,&amp;quot; which is a prepositional phrase that lacks a preceding subject/verb to make sense.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2 (DBAC):&lt;/strong&gt; This would read &amp;quot;cosmic phenomena the scientist was intrigued by the elaborate design of that shape universal laws,&amp;quot; which is a run-on and lacks proper punctuation/structure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4 (CBAD):&lt;/strong&gt; Starting with &amp;quot;that shape...&amp;quot; creates a dependent clause with no independent clause to attach to, resulting in a sentence fragment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Given below are four jumbled sentences. Select the option that gives their correct order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. For instance, the switch to renewable energy sources often faces political obstacles and financial resistance in many places.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. Rising global temperatures and harsh weather events highlight the urgent need for greater environmental awareness.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. Consequently, individual actions, while praiseworthy, alone cannot fully resolve the large-scale issues driving climate change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. Despite this growing awareness, putting effective eco-friendly practices into action on a large scale remains a big challenge.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The paragraph follows a logical progression from identifying a global problem to explaining the hurdles in solving it, ending with a concluding realization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B is the first sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it introduces the core topic and the urgency of the situation:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Rising global temperatures and harsh weather events highlight the urgent need for greater environmental awareness.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D follows&lt;/strong&gt; because it creates a direct link to the awareness mentioned in B, while introducing a complication:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Despite this growing awareness, putting effective eco-friendly practices into action on a large scale remains a big challenge.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A is the third sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it provides a specific example (&amp;quot;For instance&amp;quot;) of the large-scale challenges mentioned in Sentence D:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;For instance, the switch to renewable energy sources often faces political obstacles and financial resistance in many places.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C is the fourth&lt;/strong&gt; as it uses the transition word &amp;quot;Consequently&amp;quot; to provide a concluding thought based on the evidence presented in the previous sentences:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Consequently, individual actions, while praiseworthy, alone cannot fully resolve the large-scale issues driving climate change.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct sequence is &lt;strong&gt;BDAC&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coherent paragraph after rearrangement&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Rising global temperatures and harsh weather events highlight the urgent need for greater environmental awareness. Despite this growing awareness, putting effective eco-friendly practices into action on a large scale remains a big challenge. For instance, the switch to renewable energy sources often faces political obstacles and financial resistance in many places. Consequently, individual actions, while praiseworthy, alone cannot fully resolve the large-scale issues driving climate change.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;In spite of being exhausted, he continued working.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Although&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; introduces a concessive clause and can be transformed using the prepositional phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;in spite of&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;despite.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;In spite of&amp;rdquo; must be followed by a &lt;strong&gt;noun / pronoun / gerund (-ing form)&lt;/strong&gt;, not a clause.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;Being exhausted&amp;rdquo; correctly converts the clause &amp;ldquo;he was exhausted&amp;rdquo; into a gerund phrase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence maintains logical meaning while shifting from a subordinate clause to a prepositional construction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &amp;ldquo;In spite of being exhausted, he continued working&amp;rdquo; is grammatically accurate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;In spite&amp;rdquo; must be followed by &amp;ldquo;of.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;Despite&amp;rdquo; cannot be directly followed by a clause without &amp;ldquo;the fact that.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;Despite&amp;rdquo; is not followed by &amp;ldquo;of,&amp;rdquo; making the construction incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The article &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is used before singular, countable nouns that start with a consonant sound.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the given sentence, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;season&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a singular, countable noun, and it begins with a consonant sound.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;It is springtime, &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; season of rejuvenation in many countries.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Option 1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(&amp;quot;No article required&amp;quot;) is incorrect because an article is necessary here to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Option 2&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(&amp;quot;an&amp;quot;) is incorrect because &amp;quot;an&amp;quot; is used before words starting with a vowel sound, which &amp;quot;season&amp;quot; does not have.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Option 3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(&amp;quot;the&amp;quot;) is incorrect because &amp;quot;the&amp;quot; is used for specific or previously mentioned nouns, which is not the case here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
